Paskal Beniwoll

“We have missed several funding opportunities to expand our services in the country, leading to several issues being unsolved.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Thanks to the allocated funds, we have improved the healthcare in the country overall. I have used the resources to begin a comprehensive health reform.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Thanks to the allocated funds, we have improved the healthcare in the country overall. I have used the resources to begin a comprehensive health reform.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“The health services have been downsized and cut according to the new budget plan which caused a negative impact.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“This wouldn't be possible without your wise decision, Mr. President. So, thank you.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“However, give it a few more years and we might even surpass them.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Our privatization efforts had both positive and negative effects.”

Player

“Anybody can succeed when given all the resources. We need to do better.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“That is what I am trying to achieve.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“We should strive to do better in this avenue.”

Player

“Try to keep the problems to a minimum as best you can.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Yes, sure. But when one gets hit with the consequences of such sacrifices, it is hard to be happy about it.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Our new funds allowed us to build dozens of new hospitals around the country. We specifically focused on areas with a high demand of health services.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Not just that, we have increased our overall bed count for patients which increased the treatment capacity in many hospitals.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Thank you. I try to do my best.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“The quality of care increased due to the upgraded equipment and we were able to hire more healthcare staff.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Yes. They have been neglected for a long time due to political reasons. Not anymore.”

Player

“It better be worth the losses in capital.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Surely. With the rural incentives we have more treatment quality in those areas as well.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“The increase in salaries to all health workers was received very well.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Do not underestimate diseases and plagues, Mr. President.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Unfortunately, because of the state of our current funding, we have neither the required materials nor the capability to produce this vaccine locally.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Mr. President. You are knowingly exposing Sordland to the dangers of this virus.”

Player

“When you put it that way...Very well. Procure whatever you need.”

“When you put it that way...Very well. Procure whatever you need. [-1 Government Budget]”

Paskal Beniwoll

“You will not regret this, Mr. President. I assure you.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“We need to implement a nationwide mandatory Polio vaccination policy.”

Player

“Let's observe the situation first. We will be fine without it for now.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“Very well. I will keep you up to date.”

Paskal Beniwoll

“That was it for today, Mr. President.”
